article.headline: Auburn 96, West Georgia 72
article.story: AUBURN, Ala. -- DeWayne Reed scored 20 points to lead Auburn to a 96-72 victory against Division II West Georgia on Tuesday night. Frankie Sullivan scored 17 points and Tay Waller added 16 for Auburn (9-6), which shot 52 percent from the field (37-for-71) and outrebounded the Wolves 40-29. Waller was 4-for-7 on 3-point attempts in the first half to give the Tigers a 45-33 halftime lead. He had 14 points at the break. An 18-2 run late in the second half allowed Auburn's reserves a chance to finish the game. John Pringle led West Georgia (7-7) with 18 points and Vojin Svilar, Gavin Field and Deion Sims added 12 apiece.
